{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778556239,"nonce":"QiuvZyMW6ttq6lNeiWF724p4kZo=","message":"**Retraction of prior training-methods finding (2026-05-11)** — the MVP from `410d7ac` did not actually test what the prior comment claimed.\n\nThe prior comment said the linear tracker fails to decouple at standard training budgets. That conclusion was based on a misinterpretation of Δv. The MVP trained both architectures warmup-only (no adversarial phase) and measured test-time disturbance response, which is not Δv. Δv requires the adversarial-vs-baseline comparison within each architecture. The d448c9d discriminator was never actually tested.\n\nNo training-method cross-cutting takeaway stands from that MVP. Disregard the prior comment. See `410d7ac` for the corrected MVP design (4 models: regulator-baseline, regulator-adversarial, tracker-baseline, tracker-adversarial).","files":null}]}